modules.description: Returns the current POSIX time in days and picoseconds, retrieves the local time zone offset in seconds, and provides the clock's picosecond period when available. Operates with integer and 64-bit integer tuples to represent time values. Used for precise time synchronization and timezone-aware timestamp calculations.

Provides versioned storage and retrieval of custom data types with support for branching, merging, and conflict resolution. Operates on structured data, enabling efficient tracking of changes in distributed systems. Used to manage state in unikernel applications, ensuring consistent data synchronization across automated workflows.

Provides precise time management through integer-based time representations, enabling synchronization and timezone-aware calculations. Offers functions to retrieve current time, local timezone offset, and clock resolution. Supports operations on 64-bit integers for high-precision time handling. Can be used to implement logging systems with accurate timestamps or coordinate distributed events across different time zones.
